From 65ad297e4f2214199b0fed283d72982a6cd8fe19 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 08:34:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Dropdown panel: iPad-style top-anchored card on tablets
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Branch in dropdownpanel/Index on px2vp(width) >= 600vp. Tablet path
renders a frosted-glass card anchored to the top edge — control
center top-right, notifications top-left — over a dim tap-to-dismiss
backdrop, instead of the full-screen panel that's correct on phones.

Card box and scale are tuned per panel: control 700x1000 @ 0.5 (its
resource fonts are huge phone-style), notification 380x600 @ 1.0
(text already small). Scale anchor flips to the side the card is
on so it sits flush after scaling.

Notification.ets and Control.ets gain a hideInnerStatusBar prop that
the tablet branch sets to true — the host status bar is already
visible above the floating card, so the in-card status bar is
redundant. Phone branch keeps the original full-screen layout.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Change-Id: I438f51e8871b80d408f489bb603f9fdfe5ddd47e
